                <fr:title text="Stalk local implies affine local">Stalk local implies affine local</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-HE7H/" title="Stalk local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-HE7H/" display-uri="schm-HE7H" type="local">stalk local</fr:link> property, then for any <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the property of affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-C6GR/" title="Affine local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-C6GR/" display-uri="schm-C6GR" type="local">affine local</fr:link>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  This is trivial.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>
  For maps between schemes, the following notion of affine admissibility is extremely useful:
</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-NAP1/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-NAP1</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-NAP1/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Affine admissible classes">Affine admissible classes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  For a class of maps between <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link>, we say it is <html:em>affine admissible</html:em>, if 
  <html:ol><html:li>It is closed under compositions and pullbacks;</html:li>
    <html:li>It is <fr:link href="/schm-WURZ/" title="Affine local on the target" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-WURZ/" display-uri="schm-WURZ" type="local">affine local on the target</fr:link>.</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-AOI5/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-AOI5</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-AOI5/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Diagonalisation preserves affine admissibility">Diagonalisation preserves affine admissibility</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> is a class of maps between schemes which are <fr:link href="/schm-NAP1/" title="Affine admissible classes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-NAP1/" display-uri="schm-NAP1" type="local">affine admissible</fr:link>, then the class <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}\delta ]]></fr:tex>, where a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> belongs to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}\delta ]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  X \times _Y X]]></fr:tex> belongs to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex>, is again <fr:link href="/schm-NAP1/" title="Affine admissible classes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-NAP1/" display-uri="schm-NAP1" type="local">affine admissible</fr:link>.
</html:p>
 
   
