            <fr:route>/schm-KSRJ/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Noetherian condition is affine local">Noetherian condition is affine local</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Being <fr:link href="/schm-P1M1/" title="Noetherian and locally Noetherian schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-P1M1/" display-uri="schm-P1M1" type="local">Noetherian</fr:link> is an <fr:link href="/schm-C6GR/" title="Affine local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-C6GR/" display-uri="schm-C6GR" type="local">affine local</fr:link> property.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Since Noetherian distributive lattices are closed under quotients, the first condition of affine local is trivial. Now suppose we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigvee _{i\in  I}a_i = 1]]></fr:tex> with each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A/a_i]]></fr:tex> Noetherian. Any finite ascending sequence in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> induces inifinite ascending sequences in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_i]]></fr:tex>, which must be stationary by assumption. Since the family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{A_i\}_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> is finite, they must have a common upper bound where all sequences being stationary. This implies the original sequence must be stationary, hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is Noetherian.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>11</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-27GR/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>schm-27GR</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/schm-27GR/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Affine local for sheaves">Affine local for sheaves</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be a property of sheaves on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Then we say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>affine local</html:em>, if for any sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the property on affine opens <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> where the restriction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}_{\operatorname {Spec} A}]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-C6GR/" title="Affine local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-C6GR/" display-uri="schm-C6GR" type="local">affine local</fr:link>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>11</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-WURZ/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>schm-WURZ</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/schm-WURZ/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Affine local on the target">Affine local on the target</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be a property of <html:em>morphisms</html:em> of <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link>. Then we say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>affine local on the target</html:em>, if for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : Y \to  X]]></fr:tex>, the property on affine opens <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> where the restriction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(\operatorname {Spec} A) \to  \operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-C6GR/" title="Affine local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-C6GR/" display-uri="schm-C6GR" type="local">affine local</fr:link>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>11</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-4MZL/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>schm-4MZL</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/schm-4MZL/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Affine commutation">Affine commutation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/schm-C6GR/" title="Affine local properties" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-C6GR/" display-uri="schm-C6GR" type="local">affine local</fr:link> property on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. If there exists an affine open cover <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{\operatorname {Spec} A_i\}_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> with each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>, then any affine open of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Suppose we have an arbitrary affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact, we can cover <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> by finitely many <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex> with each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>. Since standard opens of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> form a basis, we can choose a generating family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{d_j\}_{j\in  J}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigvee _{j\in  J}d_j = 1]]></fr:tex>, and each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D/d_j]]></fr:tex> is contained in some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex>. But since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D/d_j]]></fr:tex> is open compact in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex>, it can be identified as some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i/a_j]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_j]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_i]]></fr:tex>. By assumption of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> being affine local, each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D/d_i]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>, hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
